  • Method Details

    • runForPerfTest

      public static void runForPerfTest(BatchProcessType queueType, long pollIntervalInMillis) throws com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.AlreadyRunningException, InterruptedException
      Runs the given work queue for a performance test. First ensures there are no existing work items for the work queue as these could confuse the timing information. Then runs the writer and waits for it to finish (the workers are running while the writer is running, as would happen at a customer site). Then waits until all the work items are consumed. It polls the database to check for unprocessed work item (safer than trying to ask all the threads across the cluster whether they have "finished"), using the given poll interval
      Parameters:
      queueType - the work queue to be run
      pollIntervalInMillis - how often to check the database to see if all the work items are processed
      Throws:
      com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.AlreadyRunningException - if the writer process is already running
      InterruptedException - if the thread is interrupted while waiting for the writer or the worker threads to finish

    • runForPerfTestWithoutWait

      public static WorkQueueTestStatus runForPerfTestWithoutWait(BatchProcessType queueType) throws com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.AlreadyRunningException, InterruptedException
      Runs the given work queue for a performance test. First ensures there are no existing work items for the work queue as these could confuse the timing information. Then runs the writer, but not waiting for it to finish. The client needs to call isWriterFinished() to constantly poll whether the writer is finished, then to call isWorkCompleted() to poll when all work items are consumed.
      Parameters:
      queueType - the work queue to be run
      Throws:
      com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.AlreadyRunningException - if the writer process is already running
      InterruptedException - if the thread is interrupted while waiting for the writer or the worker threads to finish

    • runWriterForPerfTestWithoutWait

      public static WorkQueueTestStatus runWriterForPerfTestWithoutWait(BatchProcessType queueType) throws com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.AlreadyRunningException, InterruptedException
      Runs the given work queue writer-only for a performance test. First ensures there are no existing work items for the work queue as these could confuse the timing information. Then runs the writer, but not waiting for it to finish. The client needs to call isWriterFinished() to constantly poll whether the writer is finished, then to call isWorkCompleted() to poll when all work items are consumed.
      Parameters:
      queueType - the work queue to be run
      Throws:
      com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.AlreadyRunningException - if the writer process is already running
      InterruptedException - if the thread is interrupted while waiting for the writer to start

    • runWorkersForPerfTestWithoutWait

      public static WorkQueueTestStatus runWorkersForPerfTestWithoutWait(BatchProcessType queueType, WorkQueueTestStatus testStatus)
      Runs the given work queue workers-only for a performance test. The writer must have been run previously by the caller. The client needs to call isWorkCompleted() to poll when all work items are consumed.
      Parameters:
      queueType - the work queue to be run
